# Cybercrime Prevention Checklist for Students

## Essential Safety Rules

* **UPI Rule - PIN is for SENDING:** Never enter your UPI PIN to receive money. You only need your PIN to send money or check your account balance.
* **UPI Rule - Verify the Receiver:** Always double-check the recipient's name that pops up on your UPI app screen before hitting confirm or entering your PIN.
* **Beware of Urgent Messages:** Ignore SMS or WhatsApp messages from unknown numbers claiming your bank account, SIM card, or PAN card will be blocked unless you click a link immediately.
* **Verify Friend Requests for Money:** If a friend or family member suddenly messages you asking for urgent financial help, call them directly on their phone number to verify it is actually them.
* **Enable Two-Factor Authentication:** Turn on two-factor authentication (2FA) for your email, WhatsApp, and all social media accounts to prevent unauthorized logins even if someone gets your password.
* **Avoid Public Wi-Fi for Banking:** Never make financial transactions, pay fees, or log into your bank app while connected to unsecured public Wi-Fi at cafes or campus lounges.
* **Keep Your Digital Footprint Clean:** Do not post pictures of your college ID, driver's license, or travel tickets on social media.

